  "answer": "- In the treatment group, $\tilde{a}_1=a_1+1=751+1=752$, $\tilde{n}_1=n_1+2= 8506+2=8508$, and $\tilde{p}_1=\frac{752}{8508}=0.08839$.
- In the control group, $\bar{a}_2=a_2+1=623+1=624, \bar{n}_2=n_2+2= 8102+2=8104$, and $\bar{p}_2=\frac{624}{8104}=0.07700$.
- $S E_{\tilde{p}_1-\tilde{p}_2}=\sqrt{\frac{\tilde{p}_1 \tilde{q}_1}{\tilde{n}_1}+\frac{\tilde{p}_2 \tilde{q}_2}{\tilde{n}_2}}= \sqrt{\frac{(0.08839)(0.91161)}{8508}+\frac{(0.07700)(0.92300)}{8104}}=0.004271$
